postcontent:
Up for sale is my lightly used Kel-Tec PLR-16 pistol chambered in 223/556. Comes in original box with manual and a 10 round magazine. Broken in with 200 rounds and runs flawlessly.

PLR-16
The PLR-16 is a gas operated, semi-automatic pistol chambered in 5.56 mm NATO caliber. It is intended to be the ideal Silhouette shooting and hunting pistol. The rifling is 1 turn in 9 inches, right hand twist. The PLR-16 has a conventional, long-stroke gas-piston operation and utilizes the proven Johnson/Stoner breech locking system. The rear sight is adjustable for windage. The front sight is similar to an AR-15 style rifle, and adjustable for elevation. An integrated MIL-STD-1913 Picatinny rail will accept a multitude of standard accessories. The muzzle is threaded 1/2-28 TPI to accept standard attachments such as a muzzle brake or flash hider. Except for the barrel, bolt, sights, and mechanism, the PLR-16 pistol is made entirely of high-impact glass fiber reinforced polymer.
TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS
Calibers:	.223rem
Weight unloaded:	3.42lbs	1.55kg
Length:	18.5"	469.9mm
Barrel length:	9.2"	233.7mm
Twist:	1:9"	1:228.6mm
Capacity:	10, or M-16 compatible
Trigger pull:	5.5-7.5lbs	24.4-33.4N
Sight radius:	12.5"	317.5mm
Muzzle velocity:	2600fps	 
The accessories available for the PLR-16 include forend with Picatinny rail on the bottom, scope rings, dynamic deflecting operating handle, single point sling, and a muzzle brake specifically design for the 9.2" barrel of the PLR-16.

title: For Trade:  WTT 1996 VW GTI 2.0 auto
postcontent:
Selling my Candy White 1996 Volkswagen GTI 2.0 ABA Automatic Transmission 3 door hatchback (5.9 Motronic Engine Management, 01MTransmission) mid June production run) little under 143k original miles on original engine and transmission. (avg 8315 miles driven per year so consider this low mileage on a 17 year old car, that being said I know my car inside and out) I have a car fax report dated January 18, 2013 for you to even look at if you come to see the car. Have my Texas title in hand ,Asking $3000 OBO ($2750 OBO less the system): no salvaged title, no rebuilt title and I have paperwork and receipts for work done from 2004-2013. Motor has never been turbo'd or super charged.

Quick history on car fax:
Even though car fax estimates about 5 owners I am actually the 2nd owner of this car from about 61k miles and have had it since January 2004. 

I have keep this car well maintained as my husband is US Army mechanic and we have done all the modifications ourselves and any major work has been done thru Volkswagen Dealerships in Indiana, Germany, Texas and Florida and Euro tech shops, such major work that has been completed within the last 3 years thru 3rd party is: 
Crank position sensor done at European Autohaus Tampa March 2013
Wheel Bearings front end alignment done at Reeves Tampa, Florida January 2013, 
Front Strut mounts January 2013 at Pep boys in Tampa, Florida,
Front control arms poly urethane bushings pressed at Eurotech in Killeen 2011,
AC restoration- compressor condenser and fluids at Garlyn Shelton VW in Temple, Texas in March 2012,
New Kuhmo xpert KH20B P 195 60R 14H tires just put on this past July 2012 at Sears automotive in Killeen, Texas. 

We have a HnR 40/60 cup kit on the car and all poly urethane bushings on all control arms and pivots it has a very stiff ride, October 2010 GSP drive axles front replaced, running mk4 calipers and stainless brake lines , had rear brakes and pads all done in June 2012 . Put on a Magnaflow exhaust this past summer in June 2012 . I have the Thule 444 specialty roof rack with 50lb load bars on the roof, Sun guard tint front(32%) thru back(darkest on rear quarter windows 05% and back hatch 05%) Audio system includes Kenwood Sirius ready cd player with usb and audio out hook ups along with JVC speakers thru out front doors and tweeters ATX 1000-2 amp Infinity amp and 10 inch CVR sub in the rear. New battery bought from Sears in 2012, We have kept up with all regular standard oil changes using 5w 20 full synthetic. Just replaced the heater core June 2012 , Replaced fuel pump relay, distributor cap and rotor, crank shaft position sensor in March 2013. Replaced Vehicle speed sensor in April 2013 as well as AC shutoff sensor and o rings. I have a stack of receipts on the purchases we have made for it thru out the years and what else we have replaced on the car. As well as my partially scanned copy of the vw gti/golf bentley manual as well as the digital copy on CD.


Cosmetic wise the car is a northern car it has some rust spotting on the rear by the tail lights when you open up the hatch, a little bit of rust forming by the driver's side window on the ledge , has rust on the bottom of the rocker panels. My clear coat is in a peeling stage on the rear hatch with every car wash I'm losing a little bit each time with the high pressure washes. I am currently missing part of my side skirts, I have been searching LKQ for golf's with them and haven't had much luck, Interior has normal wear and tear, but there is some heavier wear and tear on the front driver's seat edges. The rear hatch top cover and wheel well cover we modified in Texas with wood and pleather wrap giving it a nicer appearance and still fully functional. 

Mechanical wise things that will need to be done/ tinkered with, recently doing the struts they noticed at pep boys my coolant leak coming from the radiator, it's a very small leak but will need attention (we are adding a little bit of coolant about every couple weeks) for this fix it would be to replace the radiator and those run about 80-125 bucks if you do it yourself. The coolant pressure tank should also be replaced in the process those run about 20-30 bucks online. Reason by it the coolant light is flashing as soon as you turn on the car so pressure is not stabilized in the tank. We replaced the Vehicle Speed Sensor on the car but the gauge cluster tends to go off and on again with all the warning lights come back on so it's a bit annoying. The car is throwing the engine code p0501 which is that sensor but we replaced it with OEM part and it still has gauge cluster speedo issues not too sure what else can be cause it and I don't like tinkering with the electrical system but we replaced the clip on the back wire harness to see if that was the problem because we had noticed a broken clip but it's still being intermittent with working. Driving on bumps in the road will sometimes cause it to stop working then come back on. 

The car has its bulk history over the last 9 years that will come with it, which is always good when buying a older car. 

If you're interested in seeing and potentially buying the car please contact my husband or me Eight1Three-Seven8Nine-Six5Three9 or Two5Four-Two5One-Eight3Five5 only serious inquires please and no low ball offers ie Kelly Blue book does not accommodate for upgrades so don't low ball me your prices off of there. I am not in a Hurry to sell this ad is merely a feeler for selling the car So serious inquires only . Any additional questions you may have please email or call or text and we will answer them the best we can as well as if you want more pictures.
